## Error Handling

- NEVER swallow errors silently
- Log errors with context (request ID, user, action)
- Do not expose internal details in error responses
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes

## Secrets Management

- No hardcoded secrets, API keys, or passwords in code
- Use environment variables or secret managers
- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, PII)

## Common Vulnerabilities

<!-- CUSTOMIZE: Add framework-specific security rules -->
- [ ] SQL Injection: Use parameterized queries
- [ ] XSS: Escape user input in output
- [ ] CSRF: Use anti-CSRF tokens
- [ ] Command Injection: Never pass user input to shell commands
- [ ] Path Traversal: Validate file paths
- [ ] IDOR: Check authorization for every resource access
